main event: Five or six objects were observed in Vineyard Haven, Massachusetts, on 24 October 1957.
interesting points: One object was seen descending and ascending very rapidly,The objects were observed visually for 3 minutes,The sighting lasted for approximately 5-10 minutes, The report considered possible explanations including balloon, aircraft, astronomical, or electronic, The observation included a ground-radar indication.
sighted object: five or six unidentified flying objects
